ENTITIES AND ATTRIBUTES :

1. Student ---
Represents each registered student user on the platform.
->Attributes:
student_id (PK)
name
emai
password_hash
department
cgpa
graduation_year
bio
profile_photo
resume_id (FK, optional)
created_at
updated_at

2. Resume ---
Stores resume details and upload paths for students.
->Attributes:
resume_id (PK)
student_id (FK)
summary
experience_years
linkedin_link
file_path
uploaded_at

3. Skill ---
Contains a master list of all skills (technical and soft).
->Attributes:
skill_id (PK)
skill_name

4. StudentSkill ---
Many-to-many relation between students and skills.
->Attributes:
student_id (FK)
skill_id (FK)
proficiency_level (optional: Beginner / Intermediate / Expert)

5. Project ---
Represents academic or personal projects added by students.
->Attributes:
project_id (PK)
student_id (FK)\
title
tech_stack
description
project_link (optional)

 6. Company ---
Stores organization or employer data.
->Attributes:
company_id (PK)
name
industry
location
description
website
contact_email
created_at

7. Recruiter ---
Represents recruiters who post jobs/internships on behalf of companies.
->Attributes:
recruiter_id (PK)
company_id (FK)
name
email
password_hash
designation
profile_photo
joined_at

8. JobPosition ---
Represents job/internship listings created by recruiters.
->Attributes:
job_id (PK)
company_id (FK)
recruiter_id (FK)
title
type (Internship / Part-time / Full-time)
description
required_cgpa
salary_range
location
posted_at
status (Open / Closed)

9. JobSkill ---
Many-to-many link between JobPosition and Skill.
->Attributes:
job_id (FK)
skill_id (FK)

10. Application ---
Tracks which student applied to which job, along with status.
->Attributes:
app_id (PK)
student_id (FK)
job_id (FK)
status (Applied / Under Review / Shortlisted / Rejected / Hired)
apply_date
reviewed_date

11. Connection ---
Handles mutual interest (Bumble-style match) between students and recruiters.Connection is â€œactiveâ€ only if both sides show interest.
->Attributes:
connection_id (PK)
student_id (FK)
recruiter_id (FK)
student_interest (boolean)
recruiter_interest (boolean)
connection_status (Pending / Matched / Rejected)
created_at

ðŸ’¬ 12. Message ---
Stores chat messages exchanged after a mutual connection.
->Attributes:
message_id (PK)
connection_id (FK)
sender_type (Student / Recruiter)
sender_id (FK)
content
sent_at
read_status

13. RecruiterReview ---
Recruiter ratings and feedback for resumes or applications.
->Attributes:
review_id (PK)
recruiter_id (FK)
resume_id (FK)
rating (1â€“5)
feedback
shortlisted (boolean)
reviewed_at

14. Admin ---
System administrator for management and moderation.
->Attributes:
admin_id (PK)
username
password_hash
email
role (SuperAdmin / Moderator)
created_at

15. Notification ---
Handles alerts for important events (match, new job, status updates).
->Attributes:
notification_id (PK)
user_type (Student / Recruiter)
user_id (FK)
message
link (optional: redirect path)
is_read (boolean)
Created_at

16. AnalyticsLog (optional but useful) ---
Stores system logs or metrics for dashboards.
->Attributes:
log_id (PK)
user_id (FK)
user_type
action (e.g., Login, Applied, MessageSent, Rated)
timestamp
